      {[
        { q: "What is CUET UG 2026 and who should appear for it?", a: "CUET (Common University Entrance Test) is the mandatory entrance exam for admission to all Central Universities in India — including DU, BHU, and JNU — along with many State, Private, and Deemed universities. Any student who has passed or is appearing in Class 12 can appear for CUET." },
        { q: "What is EduShastra's Entrance Mapping Test?", a: "The Mapping Test is an IQ-based (not knowledge-based) test used to segment students into one of five percentile groups. No preparation is required. It measures innate aptitude so we can place you in the batch that matches your current ability — not the one that matches your aspirations or your anxiety." },
        { q: "What is the Apex-25 batch and how is it different from Elite batches?", a: "Apex-25 batches have a maximum of 25 students (vs. 70–80 in Elite). Each Apex batch has 8–9 dedicated teachers, creating a 1:3 teacher-student ratio. Admission is through a merit-based Entrance Mapping Test. The curriculum is adaptive — if you struggle with a topic, sessions increase automatically. Elite batches are ideal for students who want structured learning at a lower price point." },
        { q: "What does 'Lifetime Validity' mean?", a: "Once enrolled in an Apex-25 batch, you can retake the full course — all classes, tests, and sessions — as many times as needed at zero additional cost. The goal is to ensure you hit your target percentile, not just complete a course." },
        { q: "How does the Money-Back Promise work?", a: "If you complete the full course requirements and don't achieve the guaranteed percentile for your batch series (e.g., 90%ile+ for a 9-series batch, 96%ile+ for a 10-series batch), you receive a full fee refund. Specific terms are outlined at enrollment." },
        { q: "Can I start with a free course before committing?", a: "Yes — EduShastra offers a Free Live Hybrid Course for CUET that covers the full syllabus. It's completely free (original value ₹15,999). You can experience the teaching style, faculty, and platform before upgrading to Elite Plus or Apex-25." },
        { q: "Is there a CUET course for CUET 2027 as well?", a: "Yes, EduShastra offers a combined CUET 2027 + 12th Class Board program in both weekday and weekend formats. This is designed for students currently in Class 11 who want to prepare for CUET alongside their board exams." },
        { q: "How do I contact EduShastra for city-specific batch details?", a: "Visit the Contact Us page on edushastra.com, or email contact@edushastra.com. You can also find city-specific class schedules and study centre locations via the dedicated city pages linked in the 'Available Across India' section above." },
